               <head>Revenues and description of Orissa</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh94006886 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064915" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4453-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Revenue records, in Persian with raqam annotation, and description of the Province of <name key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n2015031859" type="place">Orissa</name>
                        </p>
                        <p>Comprised of 4 sections: 1) revenues and expenditure for Orissa autumn and spring Takhāqū Yīl 1112 ʿamalī; 2) index of two khāliṣah districts autumn harvest of Sichqān [Yīl] 1139; 3) contributions from the miḥālāt, villages, forts, and farms associated with Orissa 1176 faṣlī; 4) State of accounts for Orissa 1145 ʿamalī </p>
                        <p>Green leather binding with label and separate note on slip of paper: <q>Original Accounts of the Revenues of the Mogul Empire compiled for the use of the Government of Bengal by order of Warren Hastings under the superintendence of James Grant Esq. 1784, 61 volumes in Urdu, MSS</q>
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated and lacking colophon </p>
                        <p>Not foliated; estimated 150 ff. approximately </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
